name: nytimes
text:
A federal prosecutor accused Attorney General William Barr of abusing his power to sway the election for President Trump and said he was quitting, making him the third Justice Department veteran to issue rare public criticisms of the attorney general.
https://t.co/3Jhz3XChyf

name: nytimes
text:
During a rally in Georgia on Friday night, President Trump said he may have to leave the country if he loses the election. He also made sporadic references to the pandemic, trade and the economy, but most of his remarks focused on his personal grievances.
https://t.co/FmqbiRC83Z

name: nytimes
text:
Coronavirus-related deaths among Latino and Black Americans are still disproportionately high, according to a new CDC report. The findings support early data that showed the racial inequities of the virus.
https://t.co/rXKVBJ8khq
